i have use these with good results. anyone else?


> [Original Message]
> If you really want to buy taps for suspension parts you need to make sure
you 
> buy taps of nominal or smaller size.  What you want is to retain the
"Class A 
> Fit" of the threaded items or risk them loosening from vibration.  Class
C 
> Fit threads allows one to freely spin in the nut or bolt.  Class B Fit 
> threads does not spin freely, but can be hand turned easily.  Class A Fit 
> threads really needs a wrench to turn easily.  You need a 14 x 1.50mm tap
for 
> bus lug bolt holes in the drum.  Get HS or HSS marked (High Speed Steel)
only 
> taps!  They last two to three times longer than plain carbon steel taps
and 
> have far better tolerance ground.....................................


